\c 67
\d For the Chief Musician. With stringed instruments. A Psalm. A song.
\q1
\v 1 May God be merciful to us, bless us,
\q2 and cause his face to shine on us. \qs Selah.\qs*
\q1
\v 2 That your way may be known on earth,
\q2 and your salvation among all nations,
\q1
\v 3 let the peoples praise you, God.
\q2 Let all the peoples praise you.
\q1
\v 4 Oh let the nations be glad and sing for joy,
\q2 for you will judge the peoples with equity,
\q2 and govern the nations on earth. \qs Selah.\qs*
\q1
\v 5 Let the peoples praise you, God.
\q2 Let all the peoples praise you.
\q1
\v 6 The earth has yielded its increase.
\q2 God, even our own God, will bless us.
\q1
\v 7 God will bless us.
\q2 All the ends of the earth shall fear him.
